<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-10090] Salesforce doesn&apos;t support full ISO-8601 datetimes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-10090</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/camel-salesforce-component-date-time-issue-td5784399.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/camel-salesforce-component-date-time-issue-td5784399.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
When communicating old dates the timezone-offset in a ISO-8601 format contain seconds. This isn&apos;t supported by Salesforce.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
